## Code Style Rules
- Use TypeScript strict mode for all frontend code.
- Use Python type hints for all backend function signatures.
- All components must be functional components with hooks (no class components).
- Use named exports, not default exports.
- Every public function must have a JSDoc or docstring comment.
- File names use kebab-case (e.g., user-profile.tsx, auth-service.ts).
- Component names use PascalCase. Hook names start with "use".
- API route handlers follow RESTful conventions.
- Database queries must use parameterized statements — never interpolate user input.
- All API responses follow the standard envelope: { data, meta, error }.
- Write unit tests alongside implementation — one test file per module.

## Architecture Rules
- Frontend and backend are in separate directories within a monorepo.
- State management uses React Context + useReducer for global state, local useState for component state.
- API calls go through a centralized api client (src/lib/api.ts) — never call fetch directly in components.
- Authentication tokens are stored in httpOnly cookies, never in localStorage.
- Environment variables are validated at startup — fail fast if required vars are missing.
- Database access goes through a repository layer — controllers never query the DB directly.

## Feature Blocks (Priority Order)
