## Naming Conventions
- Database tables: snake_case plural (e.g., user_profiles)
- API routes: kebab-case (e.g., /api/user-profiles)
- TypeScript interfaces: PascalCase with "I" prefix for data models (e.g., IUserProfile)
- Environment variables: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., DATABASE_URL)
- CSS classes: Use Tailwind utility classes; custom classes in kebab-case if needed.

## When generating code:
- Always include error handling — no unhandled promise rejections.
- Always validate inputs at the API boundary.
- Always consider the mobile viewport — responsive by default.
- Always write the test alongside the implementation.
- Ask before adding new dependencies.
