## 2. Architecture Overview

```
{{ problem }}
|
+-- Frontend (React + TypeScript + TailwindCSS)
|   +-- Pages / Routes — one per feature block
|   +-- Components — shared UI library
|   +-- Hooks — custom hooks for data fetching and state
|   +-- Context — auth context, theme context
|   +-- Lib — API client, utilities, constants
|
+-- Backend (FastAPI or Express + TypeScript)
|   +-- Routes — RESTful endpoint handlers
|   +-- Services — business logic layer
|   +-- Repositories — database access layer
|   +-- Models — data models / schemas
|   +-- Middleware — auth, logging, error handling
|   +-- Migrations — database schema versioning
|
+-- Infrastructure
    +-- Docker — containerization
    +-- CI/CD — automated testing and deployment
    +-- Config — environment and secrets management
```

### Data Flow
```
User Action -> React Component -> Custom Hook -> API Client
    -> HTTP Request -> Backend Route -> Service Layer
    -> Repository -> Database -> Response -> UI Update
```

